    "### 1.2 SMART Clustering Objective\n",
    " \n",
    "Following the SMART framework, the clustering objective for this project is defined as:\n",
    " \n",
    "---\n",
    " \n",
    "**\"By the end of this capstone project (June 2026), segment 10,000 survey respondents into 3–6 distinct lifestyle-emission clusters based on their transport, diet, energy, consumption, and waste behaviours, enabling sustainability programme designers to tailor carbon-reduction interventions to each segment's dominant emission drivers.\"**\n",
    " \n",
    "---\n",
    " \n",
    "Breaking this down criterion by criterion:\n",
    " \n",
    "| SMART Criterion | How It Is Satisfied |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| **Specific** | Segment individuals by their carbon-relevant lifestyle behaviours (transport mode, diet, heating energy source, waste habits, consumption patterns) — not just by a single variable, but by the full behavioural profile captured across 18 input features. |\n",
    "| **Measurable** | Identify **3–6 clusters** and characterise each by its mean carbon emission, dominant transport mode, diet type, and top contributing features. Success is measured via silhouette score (target ≥ 0.30), within-cluster sum of squares (elbow method), and interpretability of the resulting profiles. |\n",
    "| **Achievable** | The dataset contains 10,000 complete survey responses with 20 columns (13 categorical, 7 numerical). No critical columns have missing values except `Vehicle Type` (67% missing — expected, as it only applies to private-vehicle users). Standard preprocessing (encoding, scaling) and well-established algorithms (K-Means, DBSCAN, hierarchical clustering) are sufficient. |\n",
    "| **Relevant** | Directly supports sustainability programme design: by knowing *which behaviours cluster together*, policymakers can design segment-specific nudges (e.g., public-transit incentives for car-dependent clusters, dietary-shift campaigns for high-meat-consumption clusters) rather than one-size-fits-all approaches. |\n",
    "| **Time-bound** | Full analysis — from data cleaning through clustering experiments to impact reporting — completed within the capstone timeline (June 2026). |"
   ]
  },
