    "#### Selected Clustering Problems\n",
    " \n",
    "Based on the feasibility/impact analysis, three priorities are selected:\n",
    " \n",
    "**Priority 1 (Primary): Holistic Lifestyle-Emission Segmentation**\n",
    "- Combines SP1 + SP2 + SP3 into a single integrated clustering on all behavioural features simultaneously.\n",
    "- Real-world emission profiles are shaped by the *interaction* of behaviours — a person who drives a petrol car, buys 40 new clothes monthly, and heats with coal is a fundamentally different segment than someone who drives but recycles extensively and uses electricity.\n",
    "- Directly serves the SMART objective: 3–6 segments capturing the full behavioural picture.\n",
    " \n",
    "**Priority 2 (Supplementary): Outlier & Extreme-Emission Detection (SP6)**\n",
    "- Use DBSCAN alongside K-Means to flag extreme emitters who may distort standard clusters.\n",
    "- Profile these individuals separately and flag them for regulatory-level interventions.\n",
    " \n",
    "**Priority 3 (Validation): Low-Emission Exemplar Characterisation (SP5)**\n",
    "- After clustering, examine the lowest-emission cluster(s) as \"positive deviance\" cases.\n",
    "- Extract their common behavioural traits and propose them as achievable lifestyle bundles.\n",
    " \n",
    "#### How Selected Priorities Serve the Ultimate Goal\n",
    " \n",
    "```\n",
    "ULTIMATE GOAL\n",
    "Reduce individual carbon emissions through targeted, equitable interventions\n",
    "        │\n",
    "        ├── Priority 1: Holistic Lifestyle-Emission Segmentation\n",
    "        │       → 3–6 actionable personas for programme design\n",
    "        │       → Captures transport + consumption + energy interactions\n",
    "        │\n",
    "        ├── Priority 2: Outlier Detection\n",
    "        │       → Flags extreme emitters for regulatory attention\n",
    "        │       → Prevents centroid distortion in main clusters\n",
    "        │\n",
    "        └── Priority 3: Low-Emission Exemplar Profiles\n",
    "                → Identifies achievable \"green lifestyle bundles\"\n",
    "                → Supports positive-framing campaigns\n",
    "```"
